      "side": 1,
      "message": "aargh, no, please don\u0027t modify the content of |layout_file| here.\n\nA SkinFile is supposed to be an immutable data structure once it is loaded, and if in the future we want to support more than 2 layouts / SkinFile, this will become problematic.\n\nA better option is to actually change the |layout| field of the SkinUi type, i.e.:\n\n1) Modify skin_ui_create() to take a direct SkinLayout parameter, following the first one (which is a SkinLayoutFile).\n\n2) Create a skin_file_select_layout() function that will select a SkinLayout from a SkinLayoutFile based on the initialOrientation name.\n\n3) Modify the caller to skin_ui_create() to use skin_file_select_layout() from the hardware property.",
